<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:41PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Paulding and
east central Polk Counties through 815 PM EDT...
At 739 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Burnt Hickory Ridge, or
near Dallas, moving west at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dallas, Rockmart, Braswell, Yorkville, Burnt Hickory Ridge and New
Hope.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
